    <worksheet name='Radar Chart - Fishing Gears'>
      <layout-options>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe WPC,Segoe UI,sans-serif'>Trawlers</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe WPC,Segoe UI,sans-serif'> Highest benthic and bycatch impact; most destructive gear type globally</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe WPC,Segoe UI,sans-serif'>Drifting Longlines</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe WPC,Segoe UI,sans-serif'> Bycatch-dominant method; major threat to sharks, seabirds, and turtles</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe WPC,Segoe UI,sans-serif'>Purse Seines </run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe WPC,Segoe UI,sans-serif'>Strong pelagic impact; encircles entire schools of open-water fish</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe WPC,Segoe UI,sans-serif'>Pots and Traps </run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe WPC,Segoe UI,sans-serif'>Passive, trap-based method; moderate impact with low habitat damage</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe WPC,Segoe UI,sans-serif'>Pole and Line </run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe WPC,Segoe UI,sans-serif'>Most sustainable method; minimal bycatch and near-zero habitat impact</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
